<content type="html" xml:lang="en-US" xml:base="http://blog.guykawasaki.com/">&lt;p&gt;I learned of the "mother of social media lists" and the "father of social media lists." Click &lt;a href="http://www.globalsocialmedianetwork.com/?page_id=201"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to see mom and &lt;a href="http://www.beingpeterkim.com/2008/09/ive-been-thinki.html"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt; to see dad. These are the most comprehensive lists of examples of social media applications, videos, blogs, podcasts, widgets, crowdsourcing, bookmarking, microblogging, photosharing, wikis, mashups, brand monitoring ad nauseum. Check them out if you don't want to feel left out. (Thanks to Ray Schiel for showing me this list.)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~a/guykawasaki/Gypm?a=cTsnGJ"&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~a/guykawasaki/Gypm?i=cTsnGJ" border="0"&gt;&lt;/img&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
